        <h1>Shopping Basket &ldquo;Splash&rdquo; &amp; Composition Analysis</h1>
        <br>
        <section>
          <h2>Quick Summary</h2>
          <p>
            This project explores <strong>basket composition</strong> and <strong>&ldquo;splash effects&rdquo;</strong> in retail shopping data. The goal is to determine which products act as
            &ldquo;anchors&rdquo; &mdash; items that, when purchased, are associated with larger baskets or higher-value co-purchases. By identifying these anchors, marketing recruitment dollars can be allocated more efficiently toward customers or product categories that generate higher ROI through expanded basket depth.
          </p>
          <br>
        </section>
    
        <hr />
    
        <section>
          <h2>Methodology</h2>
    
          <h3>1. Data Sourcing</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Open datasets such as <strong>Instacart Online Grocery Shopping</strong>, <strong>UCI Online Retail</strong>, or <strong>synthetic basket data</strong> are used.</li>
            <li>Transaction-level data includes <strong>Transaction ID, Customer ID, Product ID/Category, Quantity, and Price</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
    
          <h3>2. Data Preparation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Transform raw transactions into <strong>basket-level views</strong> (one row per transaction).</li>
            <li>Encode product presence using binary flags (1 = purchased, 0 = not purchased).</li>
            <li>Aggregate product sales frequencies to identify candidate anchors.</li>
          </ul>
          <br>

          <h3>3. Anchor Selection</h3>
          <p>Anchors are chosen using a hybrid approach:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Frequency-based:</strong> Top N most common items/categories.</li>
            <li><strong>Value-based:</strong> High-revenue or high-margin products.</li>
            <li><strong>Association-based:</strong> Items with strong co-occurrence patterns (high lift/support).</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
    
          <h3>4. Basket Composition Analysis</h3>
          <p>For each anchor:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Calculate <strong>average basket size</strong> (number of distinct items).</li>
            <li>Calculate <strong>average basket value</strong> (sum of prices).</li>
            <li>Compare across anchors to see which lead to larger or more valuable baskets.</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
    
          <h3>5. Splash (Co-Occurrence) Analysis</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Build a <strong>co-occurrence matrix</strong> of anchor products vs. secondary products.</li>
            <li>Compute <strong>probability of co-purchase</strong> and <strong>lift ratios</strong>.</li>
            <li>Visualize with <strong>heatmaps</strong> or network graphs to show strongest splash effects.</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
    
          <h3>6. Targeting Framework</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Define <strong>Expected Value (EV)</strong> per anchor product:
              <br />
              <code>EV = P(purchase) × Avg Basket Value − Acquisition Cost</code>
            </li>
            <li>Rank products/customers by EV to prioritize recruitment or promotions.</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
        </section>
    
